  "prompt": "What are the standard puzzles asked in programming interviews?",
  "response": "Here are common types of programming interview puzzles and problems:\n\n1. Array Manipulation Problems\n- Two Sum\n- Maximum Subarray Sum\n- Rotate Array\n- Find Missing Number\n- Merge Sorted Arrays\n- Product of Array Except Self\n\n2. String Manipulation\n- Reverse String\n- Palindrome Check\n- Longest Substring Without Repeating Characters\n- String Compression\n- Valid Anagram\n\n3. Linked List Problems\n- Reverse Linked List\n- Detect Cycle\n- Merge Two Sorted Lists\n- Find Middle Element\n- Remove Nth Node from End\n\n4. Stack/Queue Problems\n- Valid Parentheses\n- Implement Queue using Stack\n- Implement Stack using Queue\n- Min/Max Stack\n\n5. Tree Problems\n- Binary Tree Traversals\n- Maximum Depth\n- Lowest Common Ancestor\n- Validate Binary Search Tree\n- Serialize/Deserialize Tree\n\n6. Algorithmic Challenges\n- Binary Search\n- Depth-First Search (DFS)\n- Breadth-First Search (BFS)\n- Quick Sort\n- Merge Sort\n\n7. Dynamic Programming\n- Fibonacci Sequence\n- Coin Change Problem\n- Knapsack Problem\n- Longest Common Subsequence\n\n8. Graph Problems\n- Number of Islands\n- Course Schedule\n- Shortest Path\n- Topological Sort\n\n9. Bit Manipulation\n- Single Number\n- Reverse Bits\n- Number of 1 Bits\n\n10. Design Problems\n- LRU Cache\n- Design Parking Lot\n- Design Elevator System\n\nRecommended practice platforms:\n- LeetCode\n- HackerRank\n- CodeSignal\n- InterviewBit\n\nPreparation tips:\n- Practice consistently\n- Understand time/space complexity\n- Learn multiple solution approaches\n- Practice whiteboard coding\n- Explain your thought process\n- Handle edge cases",
